comments.body:
Change the original `input_values=[np.int64([4, 5, 6])]` to `input_values=[np.int64([4, 5, 6, 7])]`. Otherwise, there will be an error: 
```
absl.testing.parameterized.DuplicateTestNameError: Duplicate parameterized test name in InterleaveTest: generated test name 'testInterleaveDataset_test_mode_eager_tfapiversion_1_blocklength_3_cyclelength_1_inputvalues_456_numparallelcalls_None' (generated from 'testInterleaveDataset_test_mode_eager_tfapiversion_1_blocklength_3_cyclelength_1_inputvalues_456_numparallelcalls_None') already exists. Consider using named_parameters() to give your tests unique names and/or renaming the conflicting test method.
```
The cause is that when generating the test name, `dataset_ops.AUTOTUNE` will be converted from `-1` to `1`, which conflicts with the test name of the first combination (line 132 - 134)

diffHunk:
@@ -1,1 +139,143 @@                               cycle_length=7, block_length=2,
                               num_parallel_calls=[None, 1, 3, 5, 7]) +
          combinations.combine(input_values=[np.int64([4, 5, 6, 7])],
                               cycle_length=dataset_ops.AUTOTUNE,
                               block_length=3, num_parallel_calls=[None, 1]) +
